Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Install Python and pytest
    apt-get update
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3 python3-pip
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare initial filesystem state for the exercise
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------

    # Create the required application directory and files
    mkdir -p /home/user/app

    # index.html (must end with a single LF)
    printf '<html>Hello World</html>\n' > /home/user/app/index.html

    # config.yaml (must end with a single LF)
    printf 'port: 8080\n' > /home/user/app/config.yaml

    # Make /home/user writable so the non-root agent can create /home/user/backups
    chmod -R a+rwX /home/user

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author task-preparer
    Description "Environment for backup-creation task"

%help
This container provides the initial state for the backup creation task.
Pytest is pre-installed, and /home/user/app contains the two source files
(index.html and config.yaml).  The /home/user/backups directory is intentionally
absent so the agent can create it during the exercise.